### Lil Wayne Facts

  1. Lil Wayne’s original name contains the word, Dwayne. Lil Wayne dropped D from Dwayne and now uses Wayne. He told the reason, in an interview to CBS explaining “I am a junior and my father is living and he’s never been in my life. So, I don’t want to be Dwayne, I’d rather be Wayne.”
  2. Wayne wrote his first rap song at 8.
  3. At age 13, Wayne accidentally shot himself with a 9 mm handgun and the off-duty police officer Robert Hoobler drove him to the hospital.
  4. Lil Wayne’s mother, a chef, was 19&nbsp;when Wayne was born.
  5. Wayne’s second album “I Am Not A Human Being” was released in September&nbsp;2010, when he was in jail after he was&nbsp;found guilty of possessing a&nbsp;weapon and smoking marijuana.
  6. His favorite sport used to be tennis.
  7. Wayne owns a Mercedes-Benz McLaren SLR 722, which is perhaps his favorite car. It is not known if he still owns the same car or not.
  8. He refers rapper Brian Williams (or&nbsp;[Birdman](https://healthyceleb.com/birdman-height-weight-body-statistics/58800)&nbsp;/ Baby) as his Pa.
  9. He was once a member of the group “Hot Boys”.
 10. In October 2016, his prison memoir was released&nbsp;<a href="https://healthyceleb.com/refer/Lil-Wayne-book-Gone-Til-November-Journal-Rikers" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Gone Til’ November: A Journal of Rikers Island</a>&nbsp;via&nbsp;Plume Books (part of Penguin Books).
 11. Lil Wayne’s 12th studio album&nbsp;“Tha Carter V”&nbsp;was kept on hold multiple times. It was finally released in September 2018 which peaked at #1 on Billboard 200.
 12. In 2018, Lil Wayne became the first artist in the history of Billboard to have his 2 songs in the Billboard’s Hot 100’s top 5 list simultaneously. Those two songs were “Mona Lisa” featuring&nbsp;[Kendrick Lamar](https://healthyceleb.com/kendrick-lamar-height-weight-body-statistics/29616)&nbsp;and “Don’t Cry” featuring&nbsp;[XXXTentacion](https://healthyceleb.com/xxxtentacion-height-weight-body-statistics/72509).
